<item>
            <title>[LU-17971] Do not make lsvcgss record its PID</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17971</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The lsvcgssd daemon is expected to spawn a few additional threads at startup to carry out extra work. For instance with SSK, it spawns a temporary additional thread to compute the number of rounds used for Miller-Rabin prime testing. In this case finding the PID of the &apos;main&apos; thread can be complicated. So do not try to record this by ourselves, and let systemctl handle that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
